# Trivy vulnerability-gate exceptions.
#
# Policy: the gate fails on every CRITICAL/HIGH, including vulnerabilities with
# no upstream fix (ignore-unfixed is explicitly false in ci.yml). A CVE may only
# be suppressed here with an explicit, time-boxed justification — this file is
# the auditable record a reviewer or auditor reads.
#
# Format — one CVE ID per line, each preceded by a comment stating:
#   - why it does not apply or is accepted (link a VEX statement or issue)
#   - who accepted it, and the date
#   - a review-by date; expired entries must be re-justified or removed
#
# Example:
#   # CVE-2024-XXXXX — unreachable: the vulnerable code path is never called.
#   # Accepted by @alice101-dev 2026-07-06, review by 2026-10-06. Ref: #12
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX
#
# No active exceptions.
